KeyboardSwap Vision
Mission

KeyboardSwap exists to become the home of the custom mechanical keyboard community.

It begins as the safest and easiest place to buy, sell, and auction custom mechanical keyboards and components. Over time, it evolves into the platform where enthusiasts build, learn, share, collect, and connect.

KeyboardSwap is not simply another marketplace. It is an ecosystem designed specifically for keyboard enthusiasts.

The Three Pillars
Marketplace

A trusted marketplace where users can:

Buy
Sell
Auction
Trade

all aspects of the mechanical keyboard hobby.

Marketplace features include:

Auctions
Buy It Now
Make Offer
Seller verification
Buyer verification
Secure payments
Reputation
Market pricing
Community

People should visit KeyboardSwap even when they aren't buying.

Examples:

Build logs
Build journals
Collection showcases
Desk setups
Sound tests
Reviews
Guides
Featured builders
Featured collections
Monthly competitions

The goal is to become the daily homepage for keyboard enthusiasts.

Tools

KeyboardSwap should provide tools unavailable anywhere else.

Examples:

Keyboard Builder
Compatibility Checker
Market Price History
Collection Tracker
Wishlist
Saved Searches
Build Planner
Builder Marketplace

Every tool should strengthen the marketplace.

Philosophy

Every feature should answer one question:

Does this make KeyboardSwap a better place to buy, build, or learn?

If not, it probably doesn't belong.

Target Users

Primary:

Mechanical keyboard enthusiasts
Collectors
Builders
Modders

Secondary:

First-time custom keyboard buyers
Streamers
Reviewers
Professional keyboard builders
Long-Term Vision

KeyboardSwap should eventually become the operating system for the mechanical keyboard hobby.

Instead of using:

Reddit
Discord
eBay
Facebook Marketplace
GeekHack
PCPartPicker

Users should be able to accomplish nearly everything from one platform.

