Listing Creation

The listing page should be dynamic.

The first question is:

"What are you selling?"

Every category loads different fields.

Common fields remain consistent.

Additional Details always appears last.

Image uploads should support multiple photos.

Homepage

Homepage should contain:

Hero section

↓

Featured listings

↓

Ending Soon

↓

Newest Listings

↓

Infinite scrolling marketplace

Featured listings are selected by administrators.

Ending Soon should create urgency.

Search

Search should be category aware.

Keyboard filters:

Layout
Material
Mount
Switch
Hot Swap
Wireless
Price
Auction Type

Keycap filters:

Profile
Manufacturer
Material

Component filters should dynamically adapt.

Auctions

Auctions should feel exciting but fair.

Current ideas:

Standard duration
Reserve price (optional)
Buy It Now (optional)
Proxy bidding
Automatic bid increments
Anti-sniping extension
Verified payment method required before bidding
Community

Eventually users should have profiles.

Profiles include:

Seller Rating

Builder Rating

Collections

Completed Builds

Build Journals

Wishlist

Followers

Badges

Builder Marketplace

Professional builders should be able to register as builders.

Customers submit build requests.

Builders provide quotes.

Customers select a builder.

KeyboardSwap facilitates payment.

KeyboardSwap earns a platform fee.

Keyboard Builder

A future flagship feature.

Users create complete keyboard builds.

Example:

Case

↓

Compatible PCB

↓

Compatible Plate

↓

Compatible Stabilizers

↓

Compatible Switches

↓

Compatible Keycaps

↓

Accessories

The builder should use marketplace listings whenever possible.

Users can purchase an entire compatible build with one checkout.

Collections

Users should be able to showcase:

Current Collection

Wishlist

Previously Owned

Dream Builds

Completed Builds

Collections should be public.

Market Data

Every completed sale improves KeyboardSwap.

Examples:

Average Sale Price

Recent Sales

Highest Sale

Lowest Sale

Price Trend

Historical Graphs

Eventually KeyboardSwap becomes the pricing authority for custom keyboards.

Long-Term Principles

Every listing should contribute data.

Every build should improve compatibility.

Every sale should improve market pricing.

Every interaction should strengthen the community.

Every new feature should make the marketplace smarter.

